<paragraph blockId="89.[704,1233,918,1620]" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">
FIELD OBSERVATIONS: We recorded 61 captures (possibly including some recaptures) of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Koopman &amp; Williams" authorityYear="1951" box="[704,931,1315,1338]" class="Mammalia" family="Phyllostomidae" genus="Tonatia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="89" pageNumber="89" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="saurophila">
<emphasis box="[704,931,1315,1338]" italics="true" pageId="89" pageNumber="89">Tonatia saurophila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at Paracou, of which 60 were in groundÂ­level mistnets and 1 was in an elevated net. Of the 60 groundÂ­level mistnet captures, 23 were in wellÂ­drained primary forest, 26 were in swampy primary forest, 8 were in creekside primary forest, 2 were in closedÂ­canopy secondary growth, and 1 was in a manmade clearing. The only capture we recorded in an elevated net was made at 7â10 m above a treefall in creekside primary forest.
</paragraph>
